---

<DocsLayout
  title="BigQuery"
  description="Run dbt Python models on Burla instead of Dataproc Spark."
  lede="You already run production dbt on BigQuery but want your Python models to run on elastic Burla workers instead of Dataproc Spark. Skip the minutes-long Dataproc startup cost — Burla workers are ready in under a second."
  crumbs={[{ title: "Warehouses", href: withBase("/docs/") }]}
  toc={toc}
  prev={{ title: "Snowflake", href: withBase("/warehouses/snowflake/") }}
  next={{ title: "Quickstart", href: withBase("/docs/quickstart/") }}
>
  <p><code>burla_bigquery</code> wraps <a href="https://github.com/dbt-labs/dbt-bigquery">dbt-bigquery</a> and routes Python models to Burla instead of Dataproc.</p>

  <h2 id="install">Install</h2>
  <Code code={`pip install "dbt-burla[bigquery]"`} lang="bash" theme="github-light" />
  <p>Pulls in <code>dbt-bigquery</code>, <code>pandas-gbq</code>, and the Burla client.</p>

  <h2 id="auth">Authentication</h2>
  <Code code={`gcloud auth application-default login
# or:
export GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/sa.json`} lang="bash" theme="github-light" />

  <h2 id="profile">profiles.yml</h2>
  <p>Swap <code>type: bigquery</code> for <code>type: burla_bigquery</code>:</p>
  <Code code={`my_project:
  target: prod
  outputs:
    prod:
      type: burla_bigquery
      method: oauth
      project: "{{ env_var('BIGQUERY_PROJECT') }}"
      dataset: analytics
      location: US
      threads: 8

      # Burla-specific:
      burla_cluster_url: https://cluster.burla.dev
      burla_default_workers: 100
      burla_default_cpus_per_worker: 2`} lang="yaml" theme="github-light" />

  <h2 id="data">Data movement</h2>
  <p>Upstream tables are pulled via the BigQuery Storage API — the fastest path for medium tables. Results are uploaded back via <code>load_table_from_dataframe</code> (Parquet upload).</p>

  <h2 id="sql">Running SQL models</h2>
  <p>SQL models run in BigQuery as usual. No difference from vanilla <code>dbt-bigquery</code>.</p>

  <h2 id="costs">Costs</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>BigQuery query bytes</strong> for reading upstream and writing results.</li>
    <li><strong>BigQuery Storage API</strong> charges for large reads.</li>
    <li><strong>Burla worker time</strong> for the Python execution.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="caveats">Known caveats</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Partitioned/clustered tables inherit partitioning only if configured via dbt config.</li>
    <li>Regional datasets: set <code>location:</code>; the BigQuery read/write must match the dataset region.</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
